{"id": "784085", "revid": "54141843", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=784085", "title": "Wolf Pup (Warcraft III)", "text": "The Wolf Pup is a &lt;a href=\"wolf\"&gt;wolf&lt;/a&gt; used in the Blizzard \"&lt;a href=\"Warcraft%20III\"&gt;Warcraft III&lt;/a&gt;\" '&lt;a href=\"Monolith\"&gt;Monolith&lt;/a&gt;'. Because of the power of the Monolith which has been attracting wildlife with its mysterious energies, it allows a Wolf Pup to gather gold and find Wolf Dens. A Wolf Pup is the lowest level of wolf in Warcraft III costing One food and 50 gold and is classified as a worker. A Wolf Pup find &lt;a href=\"Wolf%20Den\"&gt;Wolf Den&lt;/a&gt;s allowing it to provide warmth and shelter for growing wolves and &lt;a href=\"Monolith%20Shard\"&gt;Monolith Shard&lt;/a&gt;s, becoming the Wolves only form of defensive structure. The appearance of Wolf Pup is like the &lt;a href=\"Timber%20Wolf%20%28Warcraft%20III%29\"&gt;Timber Wolf&lt;/a&gt;, but much smaller."}
