{"id": "427933", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=427933", "title": "Patch 6.2.0", "text": "Patch 6.2.0: Fury of Hellfire is the second major content patch of \"Warlords of Draenor\". It continues the &lt;a href=\"Garrison%20Campaign\"&gt;Garrison Campaign&lt;/a&gt; and is the last major content patch of the expansion.\nStory.\nHaving lured Grommash Hellscream\u2019s former lieutenants with promises of untold power, Gul\u2019dan has delivered the Iron Horde to the Burning Legion. Now, he floods the jungles of Tanaan with energies from the fallen pit lord Mannoroth, creating an army of fel orcs brimming with demonic strength and insatiable bloodlust. Even the Iron Horde\u2019s mighty war machines have been infused with fel energy, while the Shadow Council recruits fanatical arakkoa to help crush all who oppose the Legion.\nWhether Horde or Alliance, as commander of your side\u2019s garrison in Draenor you must oversee the construction of warships to assault Tanaan and disrupt the Iron Horde\u2019s frenzied preparations\u2014then stop Gul\u2019dan before his fel masters can gain a foothold on Draenor. If you fail, there will be nothing left to prevent the Burning Legion\u2019s obliteration of Azeroth.\nClass.\nDeath knight.\nGeneral\nBlood\nFrost\nUnholy\nTalents\nGlyphs\nDruid.\nGeneral\nBalance\nFeral\nGuardian\nTalents\nGlyphs\nHunter.\nGeneral\nMarksmanship\nSurvival\nTalents\nGlyphs\nMage.\nGeneral\nArcane\nFrost\nTalents\nArmor Sets\nMonk.\nGeneral\nBrewmaster\nWindwalker\nTalents\nPaladin.\nHoly\nRetribution\nPriest.\nShadow\nGlyphs\nRogue.\nGeneral\nPickpocketing\nAssassination\nCombat\nSubtlety\nTalents\nShaman.\nElemental\nRestoration\nArmor Sets\nWarlock.\nGeneral\nAffliction\nDemonology\nArmor Sets\nWarrior.\nProtection\nTalents\nArmor Sets"}
{"id": "432823", "revid": "1965082", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=432823", "title": "Patch 6.2.0/API changes", "text": "Changes.\nThe old upgradeId piece is now placed at the end of all bonusID's. If the upgradeType is 0 then the upgradeId is left off. The specializationID allows other players to view linked gear with the linking player's primary stat and set bonuses. The new upgradeType and upgradeId setup allows timewalking gear to display appropriately when linked between different level players."}
